HEADWORD: Siliceous
<hw>Si*li"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>siliceus</ets>, fr. <ets>silex</ets>, <ets>silicis</ets>, a
flint.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to silica; containing silica, or
partaking of its nature.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>silisious</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicic</ent>⟦br⟧
